388 bool ARMConstantIslands::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &mf) { 0
389 MF = &mf; 0
390 MCP = mf.getConstantPool(); 0
391 BBUtils = std::unique_ptr(new ARMBasicBlockUtils(mf)); 0
392 ----
393 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "***** ARMConstantIslands: " 0
394 << MCP->getConstants().size() << " CP entries, aligned to " ----
395 << MCP->getConstantPoolAlign().value() << " bytes *****\n"); ----
396 ----
397 STI = &MF->getSubtarget(); 0
398 TII = STI->getInstrInfo(); 0
399 isPositionIndependentOrROPI = 0
400 STI->getTargetLowering()->isPositionIndependent() || STI->isROPI(); 0
401 AFI = MF->getInfo(); 0
402 DT = &getAnalysis(); 0
403 ----
404 isThumb = AFI->isThumbFunction(); 0
405 isThumb1 = AFI->isThumb1OnlyFunction(); 0
406 isThumb2 = AFI->isThumb2Function(); 0
407 ----
408 bool GenerateTBB = isThumb2 || (isThumb1 && SynthesizeThumb1TBB); 0
409 // TBB generation code in this constant island pass has not been adapted to ----
410 // deal with speculation barriers. ----
411 if (STI->hardenSlsRetBr()) 0
412 GenerateTBB = false; 0
413 ----
414 // Renumber all of the machine basic blocks in the function, guaranteeing that ----
415 // the numbers agree with the position of the block in the function. ----
416 MF->RenumberBlocks(); 0
417 ----
418 // Try to reorder and otherwise adjust the block layout to make good use ----
419 // of the TB[BH] instructions. ----
420 bool MadeChange = false; 0
421 if (GenerateTBB && AdjustJumpTableBlocks) { 0
422 scanFunctionJumpTables(); 0
423 MadeChange |= reorderThumb2JumpTables(); 0
424 // Data is out of date, so clear it. It'll be re-computed later. ----
425 T2JumpTables.clear(); 0
426 // Blocks may have shifted around. Keep the numbering up to date. ----
427 MF->RenumberBlocks(); 0
428 } ----
429 ----
430 // Align any non-fallthrough blocks ----
431 MadeChange |= AlignBlocks(MF, STI); 0
432 ----
433 // Perform the initial placement of the constant pool entries. To start with, ----
434 // we put them all at the end of the function. ----
435 std::vector CPEMIs; 0
436 if (!MCP->isEmpty()) 0
437 doInitialConstPlacement(CPEMIs); 0
438 ----
439 if (MF->getJumpTableInfo()) 0
440 doInitialJumpTablePlacement(CPEMIs); 0
441 ----
442 /// The next UID to take is the first unused one. ----
443 AFI->initPICLabelUId(CPEMIs.size()); 0
444 ----
445 // Do the initial scan of the function, building up information about the ----
446 // sizes of each block, the location of all the water, and finding all of the ----
447 // constant pool users. ----
448 initializeFunctionInfo(CPEMIs); 0
449 CPEMIs.clear(); 0
450 LLVM_DEBUG(dumpBBs()); 0
451 ----
452 // Functions with jump tables need an alignment of 4 because they use the ADR ----
453 // instruction, which aligns the PC to 4 bytes before adding an offset. ----
454 if (!T2JumpTables.empty()) 0
455 MF->ensureAlignment(Align(4)); 0
456 ----
457 /// Remove dead constant pool entries. ----
458 MadeChange |= removeUnusedCPEntries(); 0
459 ----
460 // Iteratively place constant pool entries and fix up branches until there ----
461 // is no change. ----
462 unsigned NoCPIters = 0, NoBRIters = 0; 0
463 while (true) { ----
464 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Beginning CP iteration #" << NoCPIters << '\n'); 0
465 bool CPChange = false; 0
466 for (unsigned i = 0, e = CPUsers.size(); i != e; ++i) 0
467 // For most inputs, it converges in no more than 5 iterations. ----
468 // If it doesn't end in 10, the input may have huge BB or many CPEs. ----
469 // In this case, we will try different heuristics. ----
470 CPChange |= handleConstantPoolUser(i, NoCPIters >= CPMaxIteration / 2); 0
471 if (CPChange && ++NoCPIters > CPMaxIteration) 0
472 report_fatal_error("Constant Island pass failed to converge!"); 0
473 LLVM_DEBUG(dumpBBs()); 0
474 ----
475 // Clear NewWaterList now. If we split a block for branches, it should ----
476 // appear as "new water" for the next iteration of constant pool placement. ----
477 NewWaterList.clear(); 0
478 ----
479 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Beginning BR iteration #" << NoBRIters << '\n'); 0
480 bool BRChange = false; 0
481 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ImmBranches.size(); i != e; ++i) 0
482 BRChange |= fixupImmediateBr(ImmBranches[i]); 0
483 if (BRChange && ++NoBRIters > 30) 0
484 report_fatal_error("Branch Fix Up pass failed to converge!"); 0
485 LLVM_DEBUG(dumpBBs()); 0
486 ----
487 if (!CPChange && !BRChange) 0
488 break; 0
489 MadeChange = true; 0
490 } 0
491 ----
492 // Shrink 32-bit Thumb2 load and store instructions. ----
493 if (isThumb2 && !STI->prefers32BitThumb()) 0
494 MadeChange |= optimizeThumb2Instructions(); 0
495 ----
496 // Shrink 32-bit branch instructions. ----
497 if (isThumb && STI->hasV8MBaselineOps()) 0
498 MadeChange |= optimizeThumb2Branches(); 0
499 ----
500 // Optimize jump tables using TBB / TBH. ----
501 if (GenerateTBB && !STI->genExecuteOnly()) 0
502 MadeChange |= optimizeThumb2JumpTables(); 0
503 ----
504 // After a while, this might be made debug-only, but it is not expensive. ----
505 verify(); 0
506 ----
507 // Save the mapping between original and cloned constpool entries. ----
508 for (unsigned i = 0, e = CPEntries.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
509 for (unsigned j = 0, je = CPEntries[i].size(); j != je; ++j) { 0
510 const CPEntry & CPE = CPEntries[i][j]; 0
511 if (CPE.CPEMI && CPE.CPEMI->getOperand(1).isCPI()) 0
512 AFI->recordCPEClone(i, CPE.CPI); 0
513 } ----
514 } ----
515 ----
516 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << '\n'; dumpBBs()); 0
517 ----
518 BBUtils->clear(); 0
519 WaterList.clear(); 0
520 CPUsers.clear(); 0
521 CPEntries.clear(); 0
522 JumpTableEntryIndices.clear(); 0
523 JumpTableUserIndices.clear(); 0
524 BlockJumpTableRefCount.clear(); 0
525 ImmBranches.clear(); 0
526 PushPopMIs.clear(); 0
527 T2JumpTables.clear(); 0
528 ----
529 return MadeChange; 0
530 } 0
531 ----
532 /// Perform the initial placement of the regular constant pool entries. ----
533 /// To start with, we put them all at the end of the function. ----
534 void ----
535 ARMConstantIslands::doInitialConstPlacement(std::vector &CPEMIs) { 0
536 // Create the basic block to hold the CPE's. ----
537 MachineBasicBlock *BB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(); 0
538 MF->push_back(BB); 0
539 ----
540 // MachineConstantPool measures alignment in bytes. ----
541 const Align MaxAlign = MCP->getConstantPoolAlign(); 0
542 const unsigned MaxLogAlign = Log2(MaxAlign); 0
543 ----
544 // Mark the basic block as required by the const-pool. ----
545 BB->setAlignment(MaxAlign); 0
546 ----
547 // The function needs to be as aligned as the basic blocks. The linker may ----
548 // move functions around based on their alignment. ----
549 // Special case: halfword literals still need word alignment on the function. ----
550 Align FuncAlign = MaxAlign; 0
551 if (MaxAlign == 2) 0
552 FuncAlign = Align(4); 0
553 MF->ensureAlignment(FuncAlign); 0
554 ----
555 // Order the entries in BB by descending alignment. That ensures correct ----
556 // alignment of all entries as long as BB is sufficiently aligned. Keep ----
557 // track of the insertion point for each alignment. We are going to bucket ----
558 // sort the entries as they are created. ----
559 SmallVector InsPoint(MaxLogAlign + 1, 0
560 BB->end()); 0
561 ----
562 // Add all of the constants from the constant pool to the end block, use an ----
563 // identity mapping of CPI's to CPE's. ----
564 const std::vector &CPs = MCP->getConstants(); 0
565 ----
566 const DataLayout &TD = MF->getDataLayout(); 0
567 for (unsigned i = 0, e = CPs.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
568 unsigned Size = CPs[i].getSizeInBytes(TD); 0
569 Align Alignment = CPs[i].getAlign(); 0
570 // Verify that all constant pool entries are a multiple of their alignment. ----
571 // If not, we would have to pad them out so that instructions stay aligned. ----
572 assert(isAligned(Alignment, Size) && "CP Entry not multiple of 4 bytes!"); 0
573 ----
574 // Insert CONSTPOOL_ENTRY before entries with a smaller alignment. ----
575 unsigned LogAlign = Log2(Alignment); 0
576 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsAt = InsPoint[LogAlign]; 0
577 MachineInstr *CPEMI = ----
578 BuildMI(*BB, InsAt, DebugLoc(), TII->get(ARM::CONSTPOOL_ENTRY)) 0
579 .addImm(i).addConstantPoolIndex(i).addImm(Size); 0
580 CPEMIs.push_back(CPEMI); 0
581 ----
582 // Ensure that future entries with higher alignment get inserted before ----
583 // CPEMI. This is bucket sort with iterators. ----
584 for (unsigned a = LogAlign + 1; a <= MaxLogAlign; ++a) 0
585 if (InsPoint[a] == InsAt) 0
586 InsPoint[a] = CPEMI; 0
587 ----
588 // Add a new CPEntry, but no corresponding CPUser yet. ----
589 CPEntries.emplace_back(1, CPEntry(CPEMI, i)); 0
590 ++NumCPEs; 0
591 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Moved CPI#" << i << " to end of function, size = " 0
592 << Size << ", align = " << Alignment.value() << '\n'); ----
593 } ----
594 LLVM_DEBUG(BB->dump()); 0
595 } 0
596 ----
597 /// Do initial placement of the jump tables. Because Thumb2's TBB and TBH ----
598 /// instructions can be made more efficient if the jump table immediately ----
599 /// follows the instruction, it's best to place them immediately next to their ----
600 /// jumps to begin with. In almost all cases they'll never be moved from that ----
601 /// position. ----
602 void ARMConstantIslands::doInitialJumpTablePlacement( 0
603 std::vector &CPEMIs) { ----
604 unsigned i = CPEntries.size(); 0
605 auto MJTI = MF->getJumpTableInfo(); 0
606 const std::vector &JT = MJTI->getJumpTables(); 0
607 ----
608 // Only inline jump tables are placed in the function. ----
609 if (MJTI->getEntryKind() != MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_Inline) 0
610 return; 0
611 ----
612 MachineBasicBlock *LastCorrectlyNumberedBB = nullptr; 0
613 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : *MF) { 0
614 auto MI = MBB.getLastNonDebugInstr(); 0
615 // Look past potential SpeculationBarriers at end of BB. ----
616 while (MI != MBB.end() && 0
617 (isSpeculationBarrierEndBBOpcode(MI->getOpcode()) || 0
618 MI->isDebugInstr())) 0
619 --MI; 0
620 ----
621 if (MI == MBB.end()) 0
622 continue; 0
623 ----
624 unsigned JTOpcode; ----
625 switch (MI->getOpcode()) { 0
626 default: 0
627 continue; 0
628 case ARM::BR_JTadd: 0
629 case ARM::BR_JTr: ----
630 case ARM::tBR_JTr: ----
631 case ARM::BR_JTm_i12: ----
632 case ARM::BR_JTm_rs: ----
633 // These instructions are emitted only in ARM or Thumb1 modes which do not ----
634 // support PACBTI. Hence we don't add BTI instructions in the destination ----
635 // blocks. ----
636 assert(!MF->getInfo()->branchTargetEnforcement() && 0
637 "Branch protection must not be enabled for Arm or Thumb1 modes"); ----
638 JTOpcode = ARM::JUMPTABLE_ADDRS; 0
639 break; 0
640 case ARM::t2BR_JT: 0
641 JTOpcode = ARM::JUMPTABLE_INSTS; 0
642 break; 0
643 case ARM::tTBB_JT: 0
644 case ARM::t2TBB_JT: ----
645 JTOpcode = ARM::JUMPTABLE_TBB; 0
646 break; 0
647 case ARM::tTBH_JT: 0
648 case ARM::t2TBH_JT: ----
649 JTOpcode = ARM::JUMPTABLE_TBH; 0
650 break; 0
651 } ----
652 ----
653 unsigned NumOps = MI->getDesc().getNumOperands(); 0
654 MachineOperand JTOp = ----
655 MI->getOperand(NumOps - (MI->isPredicable() ? 2 : 1)); 0
656 unsigned JTI = JTOp.getIndex(); 0
657 unsigned Size = JT[JTI].MBBs.size() * sizeof(uint32_t); 0
658 MachineBasicBlock *JumpTableBB = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(); 0
659 MF->insert(std::next(MachineFunction::iterator(MBB)), JumpTableBB); 0
660 MachineInstr *CPEMI = BuildMI(*JumpTableBB, JumpTableBB->begin(), 0
661 DebugLoc(), TII->get(JTOpcode)) 0
662 .addImm(i++) 0
663 .addJumpTableIndex(JTI) 0
664 .addImm(Size); 0
665 CPEMIs.push_back(CPEMI); 0
666 CPEntries.emplace_back(1, CPEntry(CPEMI, JTI)); 0
667 JumpTableEntryIndices.insert(std::make_pair(JTI, CPEntries.size() - 1)); 0
668 if (!LastCorrectlyNumberedBB) 0
669 LastCorrectlyNumberedBB = &MBB; 0
670 } ----
671 ----
672 // If we did anything then we need to renumber the subsequent blocks. ----
673 if (LastCorrectlyNumberedBB) 0
674 MF->RenumberBlocks(LastCorrectlyNumberedBB); 0
675 } ----
676 ----
677 /// BBHasFallthrough - Return true if the specified basic block can fallthrough ----
678 /// into the block immediately after it. ----
679 bool ARMConstantIslands::BBHasFallthrough(MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
680 // Get the next machine basic block in the function. ----
681 MachineFunction::iterator MBBI = MBB->getIterator(); 0
682 // Can't fall off end of function. ----
683 if (std::next(MBBI) == MBB->getParent()->end()) 0
684 return false; 0
685 ----
686 MachineBasicBlock *NextBB = &*std::next(MBBI); 0
687 if (!MBB->isSuccessor(NextBB)) 0
688 return false; 0
689 ----
690 // Try to analyze the end of the block. A potential fallthrough may already ----
691 // have an unconditional branch for whatever reason. ----
692 MachineBasicBlock *TBB, *FBB; ----
693 SmallVector Cond; 0
694 bool TooDifficult = TII->analyzeBranch(*MBB, TBB, FBB, Cond); 0
695 return TooDifficult || FBB == nullptr; 0
696 } 0
697 ----
698 /// findConstPoolEntry - Given the constpool index and CONSTPOOL_ENTRY MI, ----
699 /// look up the corresponding CPEntry. ----
700 ARMConstantIslands::CPEntry * ----
701 ARMConstantIslands::findConstPoolEntry(unsigned CPI, 0
702 const MachineInstr *CPEMI) { ----
703 std::vector &CPEs = CPEntries[CPI]; 0
704 // Number of entries per constpool index should be small, just do a ----
705 // linear search. ----
706 for (CPEntry &CPE : CPEs) 0
707 if (CPE.CPEMI == CPEMI) 0
708 return &CPE; 0
709 return nullptr; 0
710 } ----
711 ----
712 /// getCPEAlign - Returns the required alignment of the constant pool entry ----
713 /// represented by CPEMI. ----
714 Align ARMConstantIslands::getCPEAlign(const MachineInstr *CPEMI) { 0
715 switch (CPEMI->getOpcode()) { 0
716 case ARM::CONSTPOOL_ENTRY: 0
717 break; 0
718 case ARM::JUMPTABLE_TBB: 0
719 return isThumb1 ? Align(4) : Align(1); 0
720 case ARM::JUMPTABLE_TBH: 0
721 return isThumb1 ? Align(4) : Align(2); 0
722 case ARM::JUMPTABLE_INSTS: 0
723 return Align(2); 0
724 case ARM::JUMPTABLE_ADDRS: 0
725 return Align(4); 0
726 default: 0
727 llvm_unreachable("unknown constpool entry kind"); 0
728 } ----
729 ----
730 unsigned CPI = getCombinedIndex(CPEMI); 0
731 assert(CPI < MCP->getConstants().size() && "Invalid constant pool index."); 0
732 return MCP->getConstants()[CPI].getAlign(); 0
733 } ----
734 ----
735 // Exception landing pads, blocks that has their adress taken, and function ----
736 // entry blocks will always be (potential) indirect jump targets, regardless of ----
737 // whether they are referenced by or not by jump tables. ----
738 static bool isAlwaysIndirectTarget(const MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
739 return MBB.isEHPad() || MBB.hasAddressTaken() || 0
740 &MBB == &MBB.getParent()->front(); 0
741 } ----
742 ----
743 /// scanFunctionJumpTables - Do a scan of the function, building up ----
744 /// information about the sizes of each block and the locations of all ----
745 /// the jump tables. ----
746 void ARMConstantIslands::scanFunctionJumpTables() { 0
747 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : *MF) { 0
748 for (MachineInstr &I : MBB) 0
749 if (I.isBranch() && 0
750 (I.getOpcode() == ARM::t2BR_JT || I.getOpcode() == ARM::tBR_JTr)) 0
751 T2JumpTables.push_back(&I); 0
752 } ----
753 ----
754 if (!MF->getInfo()->branchTargetEnforcement()) 0
755 return; 0
756 ----
757 if (const MachineJumpTableInfo *JTI = MF->getJumpTableInfo()) 0
758 for (const MachineJumpTableEntry &JTE : JTI->getJumpTables()) 0
759 for (const MachineBasicBlock *MBB : JTE.MBBs) { 0
760 if (isAlwaysIndirectTarget(*MBB)) 0
761 // Set the reference count essentially to infinity, it will never ----
762 // reach zero and the BTI Instruction will never be removed. ----
763 BlockJumpTableRefCount[MBB] = std::numeric_limits::max(); 0
764 else ----
765 ++BlockJumpTableRefCount[MBB]; 0
766 } ----
767 } ----
768 ----
769 /// initializeFunctionInfo - Do the initial scan of the function, building up ----
770 /// information about the sizes of each block, the location of all the water, ----
771 /// and finding all of the constant pool users. ----
772 void ARMConstantIslands:: 0
773 initializeFunctionInfo(const std::vector &CPEMIs) { ----
774 ----
775 BBUtils->computeAllBlockSizes(); 0
776 BBInfoVector &BBInfo = BBUtils->getBBInfo(); 0
777 // The known bits of the entry block offset are determined by the function ----
778 // alignment. ----
779 BBInfo.front().KnownBits = Log2(MF->getAlignment()); 0
780 ----
781 // Compute block offsets and known bits. ----
782 BBUtils->adjustBBOffsetsAfter(&MF->front()); 0
783 ----
784 // We only care about jump table instructions when jump tables are inline. ----
785 MachineJumpTableInfo *MJTI = MF->getJumpTableInfo(); 0
786 bool InlineJumpTables = ----
787 MJTI && MJTI->getEntryKind() == MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_Inline; 0
788 ----
789 // Now go back through the instructions and build up our data structures. ----
790 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : *MF) { 0
791 // If this block doesn't fall through into the next MBB, then this is ----
792 // 'water' that a constant pool island could be placed. ----
793 if (!BBHasFallthrough(&MBB)) 0
794 WaterList.push_back(&MBB); 0
795 ----
796 for (MachineInstr &I : MBB) { 0
797 if (I.isDebugInstr()) 0
798 continue; 0
799 ----
800 unsigned Opc = I.getOpcode(); 0
801 if (I.isBranch()) { 0
802 bool isCond = false; 0
803 unsigned Bits = 0; 0
804 unsigned Scale = 1; 0
805 int UOpc = Opc; 0
806 switch (Opc) { 0
807 default: 0
808 continue; // Ignore other JT branches 0
809 case ARM::t2BR_JT: 0
810 case ARM::tBR_JTr: ----
811 if (InlineJumpTables) 0
812 T2JumpTables.push_back(&I); 0
813 continue; // Does not get an entry in ImmBranches 0
814 case ARM::Bcc: 0
815 isCond = true; 0
816 UOpc = ARM::B; 0
817 [[fallthrough]]; ----
818 case ARM::B: 0
819 Bits = 24; 0
820 Scale = 4; 0
821 break; 0
822 case ARM::tBcc: 0
823 isCond = true; 0
824 UOpc = ARM::tB; 0
825 Bits = 8; 0
826 Scale = 2; 0
827 break; 0
828 case ARM::tB: 0
829 Bits = 11; 0
830 Scale = 2; 0
831 break; 0
832 case ARM::t2Bcc: 0
833 isCond = true; 0
834 UOpc = ARM::t2B; 0
835 Bits = 20; 0
836 Scale = 2; 0
837 break; 0
838 case ARM::t2B: 0
839 Bits = 24; 0
840 Scale = 2; 0
841 break; 0
842 } ----
843 ----
844 // Record this immediate branch. ----
845 unsigned MaxOffs = ((1 << (Bits-1))-1) * Scale; 0
846 ImmBranches.push_back(ImmBranch(&I, MaxOffs, isCond, UOpc)); 0
847 } ----
848 ----
849 if (Opc == ARM::tPUSH || Opc == ARM::tPOP_RET) 0
850 PushPopMIs.push_back(&I); 0
851 ----
852 if (Opc == ARM::CONSTPOOL_ENTRY || Opc == ARM::JUMPTABLE_ADDRS || 0
853 Opc == ARM::JUMPTABLE_INSTS || Opc == ARM::JUMPTABLE_TBB || 0
854 Opc == ARM::JUMPTABLE_TBH) ----
855 continue; 0
856 ----
857 // Scan the instructions for constant pool operands. ----
858 for (unsigned op = 0, e = I.getNumOperands(); op != e; ++op) 0
859 if (I.getOperand(op).isCPI() || 0
860 (I.getOperand(op).isJTI() && InlineJumpTables)) { 0
861 // We found one. The addressing mode tells us the max displacement ----
862 // from the PC that this instruction permits. ----
863 ----
864 // Basic size info comes from the TSFlags field. ----
865 unsigned Bits = 0; 0
866 unsigned Scale = 1; 0
867 bool NegOk = false; 0
868 bool IsSoImm = false; 0
869 ----
870 switch (Opc) { 0
871 default: 0
872 llvm_unreachable("Unknown addressing mode for CP reference!"); 0
873 ----
874 // Taking the address of a CP entry. ----
875 case ARM::LEApcrel: 0
876 case ARM::LEApcrelJT: { ----
877 // This takes a SoImm, which is 8 bit immediate rotated. We'll ----
878 // pretend the maximum offset is 255 * 4. Since each instruction ----
879 // 4 byte wide, this is always correct. We'll check for other ----
880 // displacements that fits in a SoImm as well. ----
881 Bits = 8; 0
882 NegOk = true; 0
883 IsSoImm = true; 0
884 unsigned CPI = I.getOperand(op).getIndex(); 0
885 assert(CPI < CPEMIs.size()); 0
886 MachineInstr *CPEMI = CPEMIs[CPI]; 0
887 const Align CPEAlign = getCPEAlign(CPEMI); 0
888 const unsigned LogCPEAlign = Log2(CPEAlign); 0
889 if (LogCPEAlign >= 2) 0
890 Scale = 4; 0
891 else ----
892 // For constants with less than 4-byte alignment, ----
893 // we'll pretend the maximum offset is 255 * 1. ----
894 Scale = 1; 0
895 } ----
896 break; 0
897 case ARM::t2LEApcrel: 0
898 case ARM::t2LEApcrelJT: ----
899 Bits = 12; 0
900 NegOk = true; 0
901 break; 0
902 case ARM::tLEApcrel: 0
903 case ARM::tLEApcrelJT: ----
904 Bits = 8; 0
905 Scale = 4; 0
906 break; 0
907 ----
908 case ARM::LDRBi12: 0
909 case ARM::LDRi12: ----
910 case ARM::LDRcp: ----
911 case ARM::t2LDRpci: ----
912 case ARM::t2LDRHpci: ----
913 case ARM::t2LDRSHpci: ----
914 case ARM::t2LDRBpci: ----
915 case ARM::t2LDRSBpci: ----
916 Bits = 12; // +-offset_12 0
917 NegOk = true; 0
918 break; 0
919 ----
920 case ARM::tLDRpci: 0
921 Bits = 8; 0
922 Scale = 4; // +(offset_8*4) 0
923 break; 0
924 ----
925 case ARM::VLDRD: 0
926 case ARM::VLDRS: ----
927 Bits = 8; 0
928 Scale = 4; // +-(offset_8*4) 0
929 NegOk = true; 0
930 break; 0
931 case ARM::VLDRH: 0
932 Bits = 8; 0
933 Scale = 2; // +-(offset_8*2) 0
934 NegOk = true; 0
935 break; 0
936 } ----
937 ----
938 // Remember that this is a user of a CP entry. ----
939 unsigned CPI = I.getOperand(op).getIndex(); 0
940 if (I.getOperand(op).isJTI()) { 0
941 JumpTableUserIndices.insert(std::make_pair(CPI, CPUsers.size())); 0
942 CPI = JumpTableEntryIndices[CPI]; 0
943 } ----
944 ----
945 MachineInstr *CPEMI = CPEMIs[CPI]; 0
946 unsigned MaxOffs = ((1 << Bits)-1) * Scale; 0
947 CPUsers.push_back(CPUser(&I, CPEMI, MaxOffs, NegOk, IsSoImm)); 0
948 ----
949 // Increment corresponding CPEntry reference count. ----
950 CPEntry *CPE = findConstPoolEntry(CPI, CPEMI); 0
951 assert(CPE && "Cannot find a corresponding CPEntry!"); 0
952 CPE->RefCount++; 0
953 ----
954 // Instructions can only use one CP entry, don't bother scanning the ----
955 // rest of the operands. ----
956 break; 0
957 } ----
958 } ----
959 } ----
960 } 0
961 ----
962 /// CompareMBBNumbers - Little predicate function to sort the WaterList by MBB ----
963 /// ID. ----
964 static bool CompareMBBNumbers(const MachineBasicBlock *LHS, 0
965 const MachineBasicBlock *RHS) { ----
966 return LHS->getNumber() < RHS->getNumber(); 0
967 } ----
968 ----
969 /// updateForInsertedWaterBlock - When a block is newly inserted into the ----
970 /// machine function, it upsets all of the block numbers. Renumber the blocks ----
971 /// and update the arrays that parallel this numbering. ----
972 void ARMConstantIslands::updateForInsertedWaterBlock(MachineBasicBlock *NewBB) { 0
973 // Renumber the MBB's to keep them consecutive. ----
974 NewBB->getParent()->RenumberBlocks(NewBB); 0
975 ----
976 // Insert an entry into BBInfo to align it properly with the (newly ----
977 // renumbered) block numbers. ----
978 BBUtils->insert(NewBB->getNumber(), BasicBlockInfo()); 0
979 ----
980 // Next, update WaterList. Specifically, we need to add NewMBB as having ----
981 // available water after it. ----
982 water_iterator IP = llvm::lower_bound(WaterList, NewBB, CompareMBBNumbers); 0
983 WaterList.insert(IP, NewBB); 0
984 } 0
985 ----
986 /// Split the basic block containing MI into two blocks, which are joined by ----
987 /// an unconditional branch. Update data structures and renumber blocks to ----
988 /// account for this change and returns the newly created block. ----
989 MachineBasicBlock *ARMConstantIslands::splitBlockBeforeInstr(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
990 MachineBasicBlock *OrigBB = MI->getParent(); 0
991 ----
992 // Collect liveness information at MI. ----
993 LivePhysRegs LRs(*MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo()); 0
994 LRs.addLiveOuts(*OrigBB); 0
995 auto LivenessEnd = ++MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI).getReverse(); 0
996 for (MachineInstr &LiveMI : make_range(OrigBB->rbegin(), LivenessEnd)) 0
997 LRs.stepBackward(LiveMI); 0
998 ----
999 // Create a new MBB for the code after the OrigBB. ----
1000 MachineBasicBlock *NewBB = ----
1001 MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(OrigBB->getBasicBlock()); 0
1002 MachineFunction::iterator MBBI = ++OrigBB->getIterator(); 0
1003 MF->insert(MBBI, NewBB); 0
1004 ----
1005 // Splice the instructions starting with MI over to NewBB. ----
1006 NewBB->splice(NewBB->end(), OrigBB, MI, OrigBB->end()); 0
1007 ----
1008 // Add an unconditional branch from OrigBB to NewBB. ----
1009 // Note the new unconditional branch is not being recorded. ----
1010 // There doesn't seem to be meaningful DebugInfo available; this doesn't ----
1011 // correspond to anything in the source. ----
1012 unsigned Opc = isThumb ? (isThumb2 ? ARM::t2B : ARM::tB) : ARM::B; 0
1013 if (!isThumb) 0
1014 BuildMI(OrigBB, DebugLoc(), TII->get(Opc)).addMBB(NewBB); 0
1015 else ----
1016 BuildMI(OrigBB, DebugLoc(), TII->get(Opc)) 0
1017 .addMBB(NewBB) 0
1018 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1019 ++NumSplit; 0
1020 ----
1021 // Update the CFG. All succs of OrigBB are now succs of NewBB. ----
1022 NewBB->transferSuccessors(OrigBB); 0
1023 ----
1024 // OrigBB branches to NewBB. ----
1025 OrigBB->addSuccessor(NewBB); 0
1026 ----
1027 // Update live-in information in the new block. ----
1028 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF->getRegInfo(); 0
1029 for (MCPhysReg L : LRs) 0
1030 if (!MRI.isReserved(L)) 0
1031 NewBB->addLiveIn(L); 0
1032 ----
1033 // Update internal data structures to account for the newly inserted MBB. ----
1034 // This is almost the same as updateForInsertedWaterBlock, except that ----
1035 // the Water goes after OrigBB, not NewBB. ----
1036 MF->RenumberBlocks(NewBB); 0
1037 ----
1038 // Insert an entry into BBInfo to align it properly with the (newly ----
1039 // renumbered) block numbers. ----
1040 BBUtils->insert(NewBB->getNumber(), BasicBlockInfo()); 0
1041 ----
1042 // Next, update WaterList. Specifically, we need to add OrigMBB as having ----
1043 // available water after it (but not if it's already there, which happens ----
1044 // when splitting before a conditional branch that is followed by an ----
1045 // unconditional branch - in that case we want to insert NewBB). ----
1046 water_iterator IP = llvm::lower_bound(WaterList, OrigBB, CompareMBBNumbers); 0
1047 MachineBasicBlock* WaterBB = *IP; 0
1048 if (WaterBB == OrigBB) 0
1049 WaterList.insert(std::next(IP), NewBB); 0
1050 else ----
1051 WaterList.insert(IP, OrigBB); 0
1052 NewWaterList.insert(OrigBB); 0
1053 ----
1054 // Figure out how large the OrigBB is. As the first half of the original ----
1055 // block, it cannot contain a tablejump. The size includes ----
1056 // the new jump we added. (It should be possible to do this without ----
1057 // recounting everything, but it's very confusing, and this is rarely ----
1058 // executed.) ----
1059 BBUtils->computeBlockSize(OrigBB); 0
1060 ----
1061 // Figure out how large the NewMBB is. As the second half of the original ----
1062 // block, it may contain a tablejump. ----
1063 BBUtils->computeBlockSize(NewBB); 0
1064 ----
1065 // All BBOffsets following these blocks must be modified. ----
1066 BBUtils->adjustBBOffsetsAfter(OrigBB); 0
1067 ----
1068 return NewBB; 0
1069 } 0
1070 ----
1071 /// getUserOffset - Compute the offset of U.MI as seen by the hardware ----
1072 /// displacement computation. Update U.KnownAlignment to match its current ----
1073 /// basic block location. ----
1074 unsigned ARMConstantIslands::getUserOffset(CPUser &U) const { 0
1075 unsigned UserOffset = BBUtils->getOffsetOf(U.MI); 0
1076 ----
1077 SmallVectorImpl &BBInfo = BBUtils->getBBInfo(); 0
1078 const BasicBlockInfo &BBI = BBInfo[U.MI->getParent()->getNumber()]; 0
1079 unsigned KnownBits = BBI.internalKnownBits(); 0
1080 ----
1081 // The value read from PC is offset from the actual instruction address. ----
1082 UserOffset += (isThumb ? 4 : 8); 0
1083 ----
1084 // Because of inline assembly, we may not know the alignment (mod 4) of U.MI. ----
1085 // Make sure U.getMaxDisp() returns a constrained range. ----
1086 U.KnownAlignment = (KnownBits >= 2); 0
1087 ----
1088 // On Thumb, offsets==2 mod 4 are rounded down by the hardware for ----
1089 // purposes of the displacement computation; compensate for that here. ----
1090 // For unknown alignments, getMaxDisp() constrains the range instead. ----
1091 if (isThumb && U.KnownAlignment) 0
1092 UserOffset &= ~3u; 0
1093 ----
1094 return UserOffset; 0
1095 } ----
1096 ----
1097 /// isOffsetInRange - Checks whether UserOffset (the location of a constant pool ----
1098 /// reference) is within MaxDisp of TrialOffset (a proposed location of a ----
1099 /// constant pool entry). ----
1100 /// UserOffset is computed by getUserOffset above to include PC adjustments. If ----
1101 /// the mod 4 alignment of UserOffset is not known, the uncertainty must be ----
1102 /// subtracted from MaxDisp instead. CPUser::getMaxDisp() does that. ----
1103 bool ARMConstantIslands::isOffsetInRange(unsigned UserOffset, 0
1104 unsigned TrialOffset, unsigned MaxDisp, ----
1105 bool NegativeOK, bool IsSoImm) { ----
1106 if (UserOffset <= TrialOffset) { 0
1107 // User before the Trial. ----
1108 if (TrialOffset - UserOffset <= MaxDisp) 0
1109 return true; 0
1110 // FIXME: Make use full range of soimm values. ----
1111 } else if (NegativeOK) { 0
1112 if (UserOffset - TrialOffset <= MaxDisp) 0
1113 return true; 0
1114 // FIXME: Make use full range of soimm values. ----
1115 } ----
1116 return false; 0
1117 } ----
1118 ----
1119 /// isWaterInRange - Returns true if a CPE placed after the specified ----
1120 /// Water (a basic block) will be in range for the specific MI. ----
1121 /// ----
1122 /// Compute how much the function will grow by inserting a CPE after Water. ----
1123 bool ARMConstantIslands::isWaterInRange(unsigned UserOffset, 0
1124 MachineBasicBlock* Water, CPUser &U, ----
1125 unsigned &Growth) { ----
1126 BBInfoVector &BBInfo = BBUtils->getBBInfo(); 0
1127 const Align CPEAlign = getCPEAlign(U.CPEMI); 0
1128 const unsigned CPEOffset = BBInfo[Water->getNumber()].postOffset(CPEAlign); 0
1129 unsigned NextBlockOffset; ----
1130 Align NextBlockAlignment; 0
1131 MachineFunction::const_iterator NextBlock = Water->getIterator(); 0
1132 if (++NextBlock == MF->end()) { 0
1133 NextBlockOffset = BBInfo[Water->getNumber()].postOffset(); 0
1134 } else { ----
1135 NextBlockOffset = BBInfo[NextBlock->getNumber()].Offset; 0
1136 NextBlockAlignment = NextBlock->getAlignment(); 0
1137 } ----
1138 unsigned Size = U.CPEMI->getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1139 unsigned CPEEnd = CPEOffset + Size; 0
1140 ----
1141 // The CPE may be able to hide in the alignment padding before the next ----
1142 // block. It may also cause more padding to be required if it is more aligned ----
1143 // that the next block. ----
1144 if (CPEEnd > NextBlockOffset) { 0
1145 Growth = CPEEnd - NextBlockOffset; 0
1146 // Compute the padding that would go at the end of the CPE to align the next ----
1147 // block. ----
1148 Growth += offsetToAlignment(CPEEnd, NextBlockAlignment); 0
1149 ----
1150 // If the CPE is to be inserted before the instruction, that will raise ----
1151 // the offset of the instruction. Also account for unknown alignment padding ----
1152 // in blocks between CPE and the user. ----
1153 if (CPEOffset < UserOffset) 0
1154 UserOffset += Growth + UnknownPadding(MF->getAlignment(), Log2(CPEAlign)); 0
1155 } else ----
1156 // CPE fits in existing padding. ----
1157 Growth = 0; 0
1158 ----
1159 return isOffsetInRange(UserOffset, CPEOffset, U); 0
1160 } ----
1161 ----
1162 /// isCPEntryInRange - Returns true if the distance between specific MI and ----
1163 /// specific ConstPool entry instruction can fit in MI's displacement field. ----
1164 bool ARMConstantIslands::isCPEntryInRange(MachineInstr *MI, unsigned UserOffset, 0
1165 MachineInstr *CPEMI, unsigned MaxDisp, ----
1166 bool NegOk, bool DoDump) { ----
1167 unsigned CPEOffset = BBUtils->getOffsetOf(CPEMI); 0
1168 ----
1169 if (DoDump) { 0
1170 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
1171 BBInfoVector &BBInfo = BBUtils->getBBInfo(); ----
1172 unsigned Block = MI->getParent()->getNumber(); ----
1173 const BasicBlockInfo &BBI = BBInfo[Block]; ----
1174 dbgs() << "User of CPE#" << CPEMI->getOperand(0).getImm() ----
1175 << " max delta=" << MaxDisp ----
1176 << format(" insn address=%#x", UserOffset) << " in " ----
1177 << printMBBReference(*MI->getParent()) << ": " ----
1178 << format("%#x-%x\t", BBI.Offset, BBI.postOffset()) << *MI ----
1179 << format("CPE address=%#x offset=%+d: ", CPEOffset, ----
1180 int(CPEOffset - UserOffset)); ----
1181 }); ----
1182 } ----
1183 ----
1184 return isOffsetInRange(UserOffset, CPEOffset, MaxDisp, NegOk); 0
1185 } ----
1186 ----
1187 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1188 /// BBIsJumpedOver - Return true of the specified basic block's only predecessor ----
1189 /// unconditionally branches to its only successor. ----
1190 static bool BBIsJumpedOver(MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
1191 if (MBB->pred_size() != 1 || MBB->succ_size() != 1) 0
1192 return false; 0
1193 ----
1194 MachineBasicBlock *Succ = *MBB->succ_begin(); 0
1195 MachineBasicBlock *Pred = *MBB->pred_begin(); 0
1196 MachineInstr *PredMI = &Pred->back(); 0
1197 if (PredMI->getOpcode() == ARM::B || PredMI->getOpcode() == ARM::tB 0
1198 || PredMI->getOpcode() == ARM::t2B) 0
1199 return PredMI->getOperand(0).getMBB() == Succ; 0
1200 return false; 0
1201 } ----
1202 #endif // NDEBUG ----
1203 ----
1204 /// decrementCPEReferenceCount - find the constant pool entry with index CPI ----
1205 /// and instruction CPEMI, and decrement its refcount. If the refcount ----
1206 /// becomes 0 remove the entry and instruction. Returns true if we removed ----
1207 /// the entry, false if we didn't. ----
1208 bool ARMConstantIslands::decrementCPEReferenceCount(unsigned CPI, 0
1209 MachineInstr *CPEMI) { ----
1210 // Find the old entry. Eliminate it if it is no longer used. ----
1211 CPEntry *CPE = findConstPoolEntry(CPI, CPEMI); 0
1212 assert(CPE && "Unexpected!"); 0
1213 if (--CPE->RefCount == 0) { 0
1214 removeDeadCPEMI(CPEMI); 0
1215 CPE->CPEMI = nullptr; 0
1216 --NumCPEs; 0
1217 return true; 0
1218 } ----
1219 return false; 0
1220 } ----
1221 ----
1222 unsigned ARMConstantIslands::getCombinedIndex(const MachineInstr *CPEMI) { 0
1223 if (CPEMI->getOperand(1).isCPI()) 0
1224 return CPEMI->getOperand(1).getIndex(); 0
1225 ----
1226 return JumpTableEntryIndices[CPEMI->getOperand(1).getIndex()]; 0
1227 } ----
1228 ----
1229 /// LookForCPEntryInRange - see if the currently referenced CPE is in range; ----
1230 /// if not, see if an in-range clone of the CPE is in range, and if so, ----
1231 /// change the data structures so the user references the clone. Returns: ----
1232 /// 0 = no existing entry found ----
1233 /// 1 = entry found, and there were no code insertions or deletions ----
1234 /// 2 = entry found, and there were code insertions or deletions ----
1235 int ARMConstantIslands::findInRangeCPEntry(CPUser& U, unsigned UserOffset) { 0
1236 MachineInstr *UserMI = U.MI; 0
1237 MachineInstr *CPEMI = U.CPEMI; 0
1238 ----
1239 // Check to see if the CPE is already in-range. ----
1240 if (isCPEntryInRange(UserMI, UserOffset, CPEMI, U.getMaxDisp(), U.NegOk, 0
1241 true)) { ----
1242 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "In range\n"); 0
1243 return 1; 0
1244 } ----
1245 ----
1246 // No. Look for previously created clones of the CPE that are in range. ----
1247 unsigned CPI = getCombinedIndex(CPEMI); 0
1248 std::vector &CPEs = CPEntries[CPI]; 0
1249 for (CPEntry &CPE : CPEs) { 0
1250 // We already tried this one ----
1251 if (CPE.CPEMI == CPEMI) 0
1252 continue; 0
1253 // Removing CPEs can leave empty entries, skip ----
1254 if (CPE.CPEMI == nullptr) 0
1255 continue; 0
1256 if (isCPEntryInRange(UserMI, UserOffset, CPE.CPEMI, U.getMaxDisp(), 0
1257 U.NegOk)) { 0
1258 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Replacing CPE#" << CPI << " with CPE#" << CPE.CPI 0
1259 << "\n"); ----
1260 // Point the CPUser node to the replacement ----
1261 U.CPEMI = CPE.CPEMI; 0
1262 // Change the CPI in the instruction operand to refer to the clone. ----
1263 for (MachineOperand &MO : UserMI->operands()) 0
1264 if (MO.isCPI()) { 0
1265 MO.setIndex(CPE.CPI); 0
1266 break; 0
1267 } ----
1268 // Adjust the refcount of the clone... ----
1269 CPE.RefCount++; 0
1270 // ...and the original. If we didn't remove the old entry, none of the ----
1271 // addresses changed, so we don't need another pass. ----
1272 return decrementCPEReferenceCount(CPI, CPEMI) ? 2 : 1; 0
1273 } ----
1274 } ----
1275 return 0; 0
1276 } ----
1277 ----
1278 /// getUnconditionalBrDisp - Returns the maximum displacement that can fit in ----
1279 /// the specific unconditional branch instruction. ----
1280 static inline unsigned getUnconditionalBrDisp(int Opc) { 0
1281 switch (Opc) { 0
1282 case ARM::tB: 0
1283 return ((1<<10)-1)*2; 0
1284 case ARM::t2B: 0
1285 return ((1<<23)-1)*2; 0
1286 default: 0
1287 break; 0
1288 } ----
1289 ----
1290 return ((1<<23)-1)*4; 0
1291 } ----
1292 ----
1293 /// findAvailableWater - Look for an existing entry in the WaterList in which ----
1294 /// we can place the CPE referenced from U so it's within range of U's MI. ----
1295 /// Returns true if found, false if not. If it returns true, WaterIter ----
1296 /// is set to the WaterList entry. For Thumb, prefer water that will not ----
1297 /// introduce padding to water that will. To ensure that this pass ----
1298 /// terminates, the CPE location for a particular CPUser is only allowed to ----
1299 /// move to a lower address, so search backward from the end of the list and ----
1300 /// prefer the first water that is in range. ----
1301 bool ARMConstantIslands::findAvailableWater(CPUser &U, unsigned UserOffset, 0
1302 water_iterator &WaterIter, ----
1303 bool CloserWater) { ----
1304 if (WaterList.empty()) 0
1305 return false; 0
1306 ----
1307 unsigned BestGrowth = ~0u; 0
1308 // The nearest water without splitting the UserBB is right after it. ----
1309 // If the distance is still large (we have a big BB), then we need to split it ----
1310 // if we don't converge after certain iterations. This helps the following ----
1311 // situation to converge: ----
1312 // BB0: ----
1313 // Big BB ----
1314 // BB1: ----
1315 // Constant Pool ----
1316 // When a CP access is out of range, BB0 may be used as water. However, ----
1317 // inserting islands between BB0 and BB1 makes other accesses out of range. ----
1318 MachineBasicBlock *UserBB = U.MI->getParent(); 0
1319 BBInfoVector &BBInfo = BBUtils->getBBInfo(); 0
1320 const Align CPEAlign = getCPEAlign(U.CPEMI); 0
1321 unsigned MinNoSplitDisp = BBInfo[UserBB->getNumber()].postOffset(CPEAlign); 0
1322 if (CloserWater && MinNoSplitDisp > U.getMaxDisp() / 2) 0
1323 return false; 0
1324 for (water_iterator IP = std::prev(WaterList.end()), B = WaterList.begin();; 0
1325 --IP) { 0
1326 MachineBasicBlock* WaterBB = *IP; 0
1327 // Check if water is in range and is either at a lower address than the ----
1328 // current "high water mark" or a new water block that was created since ----
1329 // the previous iteration by inserting an unconditional branch. In the ----
1330 // latter case, we want to allow resetting the high water mark back to ----
1331 // this new water since we haven't seen it before. Inserting branches ----
1332 // should be relatively uncommon and when it does happen, we want to be ----
1333 // sure to take advantage of it for all the CPEs near that block, so that ----
1334 // we don't insert more branches than necessary. ----
1335 // When CloserWater is true, we try to find the lowest address after (or ----
1336 // equal to) user MI's BB no matter of padding growth. ----
1337 unsigned Growth; ----
1338 if (isWaterInRange(UserOffset, WaterBB, U, Growth) && 0
1339 (WaterBB->getNumber() < U.HighWaterMark->getNumber() || 0
1340 NewWaterList.count(WaterBB) || WaterBB == U.MI->getParent()) && 0
1341 Growth < BestGrowth) { 0
1342 // This is the least amount of required padding seen so far. ----
1343 BestGrowth = Growth; 0
1344 WaterIter = IP; 0
1345 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Found water after " << printMBBReference(*WaterBB) 0
1346 << " Growth=" << Growth << '\n'); ----
1347 ----
1348 if (CloserWater && WaterBB == U.MI->getParent()) 0
1349 return true; 0
1350 // Keep looking unless it is perfect and we're not looking for the lowest ----
1351 // possible address. ----
1352 if (!CloserWater && BestGrowth == 0) 0
1353 return true; 0
1354 } ----
1355 if (IP == B) 0
1356 break; 0
1357 } 0
1358 return BestGrowth != ~0u; 0
1359 } ----
1360 ----
1361 /// createNewWater - No existing WaterList entry will work for ----
1362 /// CPUsers[CPUserIndex], so create a place to put the CPE. The end of the ----
1363 /// block is used if in range, and the conditional branch munged so control ----
1364 /// flow is correct. Otherwise the block is split to create a hole with an ----
1365 /// unconditional branch around it. In either case NewMBB is set to a ----
1366 /// block following which the new island can be inserted (the WaterList ----
1367 /// is not adjusted). ----
1368 void ARMConstantIslands::createNewWater(unsigned CPUserIndex, 0
1369 unsigned UserOffset, ----
1370 MachineBasicBlock *&NewMBB) { ----
1371 CPUser &U = CPUsers[CPUserIndex]; 0
1372 MachineInstr *UserMI = U.MI; 0
1373 MachineInstr *CPEMI = U.CPEMI; 0
1374 const Align CPEAlign = getCPEAlign(CPEMI); 0
1375 MachineBasicBlock *UserMBB = UserMI->getParent(); 0
1376 BBInfoVector &BBInfo = BBUtils->getBBInfo(); 0
1377 const BasicBlockInfo &UserBBI = BBInfo[UserMBB->getNumber()]; 0
1378 ----
1379 // If the block does not end in an unconditional branch already, and if the ----
1380 // end of the block is within range, make new water there. (The addition ----
1381 // below is for the unconditional branch we will be adding: 4 bytes on ARM + ----
1382 // Thumb2, 2 on Thumb1. ----
1383 if (BBHasFallthrough(UserMBB)) { 0
1384 // Size of branch to insert. ----
1385 unsigned Delta = isThumb1 ? 2 : 4; 0
1386 // Compute the offset where the CPE will begin. ----
1387 unsigned CPEOffset = UserBBI.postOffset(CPEAlign) + Delta; 0
1388 ----
1389 if (isOffsetInRange(UserOffset, CPEOffset, U)) { 0
1390 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Split at end of " << printMBBReference(*UserMBB) 0
1391 << format(", expected CPE offset %#x\n", CPEOffset)); ----
1392 NewMBB = &*++UserMBB->getIterator(); 0
1393 // Add an unconditional branch from UserMBB to fallthrough block. Record ----
1394 // it for branch lengthening; this new branch will not get out of range, ----
1395 // but if the preceding conditional branch is out of range, the targets ----
1396 // will be exchanged, and the altered branch may be out of range, so the ----
1397 // machinery has to know about it. ----
1398 int UncondBr = isThumb ? ((isThumb2) ? ARM::t2B : ARM::tB) : ARM::B; 0
1399 if (!isThumb) 0
1400 BuildMI(UserMBB, DebugLoc(), TII->get(UncondBr)).addMBB(NewMBB); 0
1401 else ----
1402 BuildMI(UserMBB, DebugLoc(), TII->get(UncondBr)) 0
1403 .addMBB(NewMBB) 0
1404 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1405 unsigned MaxDisp = getUnconditionalBrDisp(UncondBr); 0
1406 ImmBranches.push_back(ImmBranch(&UserMBB->back(), 0
1407 MaxDisp, false, UncondBr)); ----
1408 BBUtils->computeBlockSize(UserMBB); 0
1409 BBUtils->adjustBBOffsetsAfter(UserMBB); 0
1410 return; 0
1411 } ----
1412 } ----
1413 ----
1414 // What a big block. Find a place within the block to split it. This is a ----
1415 // little tricky on Thumb1 since instructions are 2 bytes and constant pool ----
1416 // entries are 4 bytes: if instruction I references island CPE, and ----
1417 // instruction I+1 references CPE', it will not work well to put CPE as far ----
1418 // forward as possible, since then CPE' cannot immediately follow it (that ----
1419 // location is 2 bytes farther away from I+1 than CPE was from I) and we'd ----
1420 // need to create a new island. So, we make a first guess, then walk through ----
1421 // the instructions between the one currently being looked at and the ----
1422 // possible insertion point, and make sure any other instructions that ----
1423 // reference CPEs will be able to use the same island area; if not, we back ----
1424 // up the insertion point. ----
1425 ----
1426 // Try to split the block so it's fully aligned. Compute the latest split ----
1427 // point where we can add a 4-byte branch instruction, and then align to ----
1428 // Align which is the largest possible alignment in the function. ----
1429 const Align Align = MF->getAlignment(); 0
1430 assert(Align >= CPEAlign && "Over-aligned constant pool entry"); 0
1431 unsigned KnownBits = UserBBI.internalKnownBits(); 0
1432 unsigned UPad = UnknownPadding(Align, KnownBits); 0
1433 unsigned BaseInsertOffset = UserOffset + U.getMaxDisp() - UPad; 0
1434 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << format("Split in middle of big block before %#x", 0
1435 BaseInsertOffset)); ----
1436 ----
1437 // The 4 in the following is for the unconditional branch we'll be inserting ----
1438 // (allows for long branch on Thumb1). Alignment of the island is handled ----
1439 // inside isOffsetInRange. ----
1440 BaseInsertOffset -= 4; 0
1441 ----
1442 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << format(", adjusted to %#x", BaseInsertOffset) 0
1443 << " la=" << Log2(Align) << " kb=" << KnownBits ----
1444 << " up=" << UPad << '\n'); ----
1445 ----
1446 // This could point off the end of the block if we've already got constant ----
1447 // pool entries following this block; only the last one is in the water list. ----
1448 // Back past any possible branches (allow for a conditional and a maximally ----
1449 // long unconditional). ----
1450 if (BaseInsertOffset + 8 >= UserBBI.postOffset()) { 0
1451 // Ensure BaseInsertOffset is larger than the offset of the instruction ----
1452 // following UserMI so that the loop which searches for the split point ----
1453 // iterates at least once. ----
1454 BaseInsertOffset = 0
1455 std::max(UserBBI.postOffset() - UPad - 8, 0
1456 UserOffset + TII->getInstSizeInBytes(*UserMI) + 1); 0
1457 // If the CP is referenced(ie, UserOffset) is in first four instructions ----
1458 // after IT, this recalculated BaseInsertOffset could be in the middle of ----
1459 // an IT block. If it is, change the BaseInsertOffset to just after the ----
1460 // IT block. This still make the CP Entry is in range becuase of the ----
1461 // following reasons. ----
1462 // 1. The initial BaseseInsertOffset calculated is (UserOffset + ----
1463 // U.getMaxDisp() - UPad). ----
1464 // 2. An IT block is only at most 4 instructions plus the "it" itself (18 ----
1465 // bytes). ----
1466 // 3. All the relevant instructions support much larger Maximum ----
1467 // displacement. ----
1468 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I = UserMI; 0
1469 ++I; 0
1470 Register PredReg; 0
1471 for (unsigned Offset = UserOffset + TII->getInstSizeInBytes(*UserMI); 0
1472 I->getOpcode() != ARM::t2IT && 0
1473 getITInstrPredicate(*I, PredReg) != ARMCC::AL; 0
1474 Offset += TII->getInstSizeInBytes(*I), I = std::next(I)) { 0
1475 BaseInsertOffset = 0
1476 std::max(BaseInsertOffset, Offset + TII->getInstSizeInBytes(*I) + 1); 0
1477 assert(I != UserMBB->end() && "Fell off end of block"); 0
1478 } ----
1479 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << format("Move inside block: %#x\n", BaseInsertOffset)); 0
1480 } ----
1481 unsigned EndInsertOffset = BaseInsertOffset + 4 + UPad + 0
1482 CPEMI->getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1483 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MI = UserMI; 0
1484 ++MI; 0
1485 unsigned CPUIndex = CPUserIndex+1; 0
1486 unsigned NumCPUsers = CPUsers.size(); 0
1487 MachineInstr *LastIT = nullptr; 0
1488 for (unsigned Offset = UserOffset + TII->getInstSizeInBytes(*UserMI); 0
1489 Offset < BaseInsertOffset; 0
1490 Offset += TII->getInstSizeInBytes(*MI), MI = std::next(MI)) { 0
1491 assert(MI != UserMBB->end() && "Fell off end of block"); 0
1492 if (CPUIndex < NumCPUsers && CPUsers[CPUIndex].MI == &*MI) { 0
1493 CPUser &U = CPUsers[CPUIndex]; 0
1494 if (!isOffsetInRange(Offset, EndInsertOffset, U)) { 0
1495 // Shift intertion point by one unit of alignment so it is within reach. ----
1496 BaseInsertOffset -= Align.value(); 0
1497 EndInsertOffset -= Align.value(); 0
1498 } ----
1499 // This is overly conservative, as we don't account for CPEMIs being ----
1500 // reused within the block, but it doesn't matter much. Also assume CPEs ----
1501 // are added in order with alignment padding. We may eventually be able ----
1502 // to pack the aligned CPEs better. ----
1503 EndInsertOffset += U.CPEMI->getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1504 CPUIndex++; 0
1505 } ----
1506 ----
1507 // Remember the last IT instruction. ----
1508 if (MI->getOpcode() == ARM::t2IT) 0
1509 LastIT = &*MI; 0
1510 } ----
1511 ----
1512 --MI; 0
1513 ----
1514 // Avoid splitting an IT block. ----
1515 if (LastIT) { 0
1516 Register PredReg; 0
1517 ARMCC::CondCodes CC = getITInstrPredicate(*MI, PredReg); 0
1518 if (CC != ARMCC::AL) 0
1519 MI = LastIT; 0
1520 } ----
1521 ----
1522 // Avoid splitting a MOVW+MOVT pair with a relocation on Windows. ----
1523 // On Windows, this instruction pair is covered by one single ----
1524 // IMAGE_REL_ARM_MOV32T relocation which covers both instructions. If a ----
1525 // constant island is injected inbetween them, the relocation will clobber ----
1526 // the instruction and fail to update the MOVT instruction. ----
1527 // (These instructions are bundled up until right before the ConstantIslands ----
1528 // pass.) ----
1529 if (STI->isTargetWindows() && isThumb && MI->getOpcode() == ARM::t2MOVTi16 && 0
1530 (MI->getOperand(2).getTargetFlags() & ARMII::MO_OPTION_MASK) == 0
1531 ARMII::MO_HI16) { ----
1532 --MI; 0
1533 assert(MI->getOpcode() == ARM::t2MOVi16 && 0
1534 (MI->getOperand(1).getTargetFlags() & ARMII::MO_OPTION_MASK) == ----
1535 ARMII::MO_LO16); ----
1536 } ----
1537 ----
1538 // We really must not split an IT block. ----
1539 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1540 Register PredReg; 0
1541 assert(!isThumb || getITInstrPredicate(*MI, PredReg) == ARMCC::AL); 0
1542 #endif ----
1543 NewMBB = splitBlockBeforeInstr(&*MI); 0
1544 } ----
1545 ----
1546 /// handleConstantPoolUser - Analyze the specified user, checking to see if it ----
1547 /// is out-of-range. If so, pick up the constant pool value and move it some ----
1548 /// place in-range. Return true if we changed any addresses (thus must run ----
1549 /// another pass of branch lengthening), false otherwise. ----
1550 bool ARMConstantIslands::handleConstantPoolUser(unsigned CPUserIndex, 0
1551 bool CloserWater) { ----
1552 CPUser &U = CPUsers[CPUserIndex]; 0
1553 MachineInstr *UserMI = U.MI; 0
1554 MachineInstr *CPEMI = U.CPEMI; 0
1555 unsigned CPI = getCombinedIndex(CPEMI); 0
1556 unsigned Size = CPEMI->getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1557 // Compute this only once, it's expensive. ----
1558 unsigned UserOffset = getUserOffset(U); 0
1559 ----
1560 // See if the current entry is within range, or there is a clone of it ----
1561 // in range. ----
1562 int result = findInRangeCPEntry(U, UserOffset); 0
1563 if (result==1) return false; 0
1564 else if (result==2) return true; 0
1565 ----
1566 // No existing clone of this CPE is within range. ----
1567 // We will be generating a new clone. Get a UID for it. ----
1568 unsigned ID = AFI->createPICLabelUId(); 0
1569 ----
1570 // Look for water where we can place this CPE. ----
1571 MachineBasicBlock *NewIsland = MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(); 0
1572 MachineBasicBlock *NewMBB; ----
1573 water_iterator IP; 0
1574 if (findAvailableWater(U, UserOffset, IP, CloserWater)) { 0
1575 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Found water in range\n"); 0
1576 MachineBasicBlock *WaterBB = *IP; 0
1577 ----
1578 // If the original WaterList entry was "new water" on this iteration, ----
1579 // propagate that to the new island. This is just keeping NewWaterList ----
1580 // updated to match the WaterList, which will be updated below. ----
1581 if (NewWaterList.erase(WaterBB)) 0
1582 NewWaterList.insert(NewIsland); 0
1583 ----
1584 // The new CPE goes before the following block (NewMBB). ----
1585 NewMBB = &*++WaterBB->getIterator(); 0
1586 } else { ----
1587 // No water found. ----
1588 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "No water found\n"); 0
1589 createNewWater(CPUserIndex, UserOffset, NewMBB); 0
1590 ----
1591 // splitBlockBeforeInstr adds to WaterList, which is important when it is ----
1592 // called while handling branches so that the water will be seen on the ----
1593 // next iteration for constant pools, but in this context, we don't want ----
1594 // it. Check for this so it will be removed from the WaterList. ----
1595 // Also remove any entry from NewWaterList. ----
1596 MachineBasicBlock *WaterBB = &*--NewMBB->getIterator(); 0
1597 IP = find(WaterList, WaterBB); 0
1598 if (IP != WaterList.end()) 0
1599 NewWaterList.erase(WaterBB); 0
1600 ----
1601 // We are adding new water. Update NewWaterList. ----
1602 NewWaterList.insert(NewIsland); 0
1603 } ----
1604 // Always align the new block because CP entries can be smaller than 4 ----
1605 // bytes. Be careful not to decrease the existing alignment, e.g. NewMBB may ----
1606 // be an already aligned constant pool block. ----
1607 const Align Alignment = isThumb ? Align(2) : Align(4); 0
1608 if (NewMBB->getAlignment() < Alignment) 0
1609 NewMBB->setAlignment(Alignment); 0
1610 ----
1611 // Remove the original WaterList entry; we want subsequent insertions in ----
1612 // this vicinity to go after the one we're about to insert. This ----
1613 // considerably reduces the number of times we have to move the same CPE ----
1614 // more than once and is also important to ensure the algorithm terminates. ----
1615 if (IP != WaterList.end()) 0
1616 WaterList.erase(IP); 0
1617 ----
1618 // Okay, we know we can put an island before NewMBB now, do it! ----
1619 MF->insert(NewMBB->getIterator(), NewIsland); 0
1620 ----
1621 // Update internal data structures to account for the newly inserted MBB. ----
1622 updateForInsertedWaterBlock(NewIsland); 0
1623 ----
1624 // Now that we have an island to add the CPE to, clone the original CPE and ----
1625 // add it to the island. ----
1626 U.HighWaterMark = NewIsland; 0
1627 U.CPEMI = BuildMI(NewIsland, DebugLoc(), CPEMI->getDesc()) 0
1628 .addImm(ID) 0
1629 .add(CPEMI->getOperand(1)) 0
1630 .addImm(Size); 0
1631 CPEntries[CPI].push_back(CPEntry(U.CPEMI, ID, 1)); 0
1632 ++NumCPEs; 0
1633 ----
1634 // Decrement the old entry, and remove it if refcount becomes 0. ----
1635 decrementCPEReferenceCount(CPI, CPEMI); 0
1636 ----
1637 // Mark the basic block as aligned as required by the const-pool entry. ----
1638 NewIsland->setAlignment(getCPEAlign(U.CPEMI)); 0
1639 ----
1640 // Increase the size of the island block to account for the new entry. ----
1641 BBUtils->adjustBBSize(NewIsland, Size); 0
1642 BBUtils->adjustBBOffsetsAfter(&*--NewIsland->getIterator()); 0
1643 ----
1644 // Finally, change the CPI in the instruction operand to be ID. ----
1645 for (MachineOperand &MO : UserMI->operands()) 0
1646 if (MO.isCPI()) { 0
1647 MO.setIndex(ID); 0
1648 break; 0
1649 } ----
1650 ----
1651 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1652 dbgs() << " Moved CPE to #" << ID << " CPI=" << CPI ----
1653 << format(" offset=%#x\n", ----
1654 BBUtils->getBBInfo()[NewIsland->getNumber()].Offset)); ----
1655 ----
1656 return true; 0
1657 } ----
1658 ----
1659 /// removeDeadCPEMI - Remove a dead constant pool entry instruction. Update ----
1660 /// sizes and offsets of impacted basic blocks. ----
1661 void ARMConstantIslands::removeDeadCPEMI(MachineInstr *CPEMI) { 0
1662 MachineBasicBlock *CPEBB = CPEMI->getParent(); 0
1663 unsigned Size = CPEMI->getOperand(2).getImm(); 0
1664 CPEMI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1665 BBInfoVector &BBInfo = BBUtils->getBBInfo(); 0
1666 BBUtils->adjustBBSize(CPEBB, -Size); 0
1667 // All succeeding offsets have the current size value added in, fix this. ----
1668 if (CPEBB->empty()) { 0
1669 BBInfo[CPEBB->getNumber()].Size = 0; 0
1670 ----
1671 // This block no longer needs to be aligned. ----
1672 CPEBB->setAlignment(Align(1)); 0
1673 } else { ----
1674 // Entries are sorted by descending alignment, so realign from the front. ----
1675 CPEBB->setAlignment(getCPEAlign(&*CPEBB->begin())); 0
1676 } ----
1677 ----
1678 BBUtils->adjustBBOffsetsAfter(CPEBB); 0
1679 // An island has only one predecessor BB and one successor BB. Check if ----
1680 // this BB's predecessor jumps directly to this BB's successor. This ----
1681 // shouldn't happen currently. ----
1682 assert(!BBIsJumpedOver(CPEBB) && "How did this happen?"); 0
1683 // FIXME: remove the empty blocks after all the work is done? ----
1684 } 0
1685 ----
1686 /// removeUnusedCPEntries - Remove constant pool entries whose refcounts ----
1687 /// are zero. ----
1688 bool ARMConstantIslands::removeUnusedCPEntries() { 0
1689 unsigned MadeChange = false; 0
1690 for (std::vector &CPEs : CPEntries) { 0
1691 for (CPEntry &CPE : CPEs) { 0
1692 if (CPE.RefCount == 0 && CPE.CPEMI) { 0
1693 removeDeadCPEMI(CPE.CPEMI); 0
1694 CPE.CPEMI = nullptr; 0
1695 MadeChange = true; 0
1696 } ----
1697 } ----
1698 } ----
1699 return MadeChange; 0
1700 } ----
1701 ----
1702 ----
1703 /// fixupImmediateBr - Fix up an immediate branch whose destination is too far ----
1704 /// away to fit in its displacement field. ----
1705 bool ARMConstantIslands::fixupImmediateBr(ImmBranch &Br) { 0
1706 MachineInstr *MI = Br.MI; 0
1707 MachineBasicBlock *DestBB = MI->getOperand(0).getMBB(); 0
1708 ----
1709 // Check to see if the DestBB is already in-range. ----
1710 if (BBUtils->isBBInRange(MI, DestBB, Br.MaxDisp)) 0
1711 return false; 0
1712 ----
1713 if (!Br.isCond) 0
1714 return fixupUnconditionalBr(Br); 0
1715 return fixupConditionalBr(Br); 0
1716 } ----
1717 ----
1718 /// fixupUnconditionalBr - Fix up an unconditional branch whose destination is ----
1719 /// too far away to fit in its displacement field. If the LR register has been ----
1720 /// spilled in the epilogue, then we can use BL to implement a far jump. ----
1721 /// Otherwise, add an intermediate branch instruction to a branch. ----
1722 bool ----
1723 ARMConstantIslands::fixupUnconditionalBr(ImmBranch &Br) { 0
1724 MachineInstr *MI = Br.MI; 0
1725 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI->getParent(); 0
1726 if (!isThumb1) 0
1727 llvm_unreachable("fixupUnconditionalBr is Thumb1 only!"); 0
1728 ----
1729 if (!AFI->isLRSpilled()) 0
1730 report_fatal_error("underestimated function size"); 0
1731 ----
1732 // Use BL to implement far jump. ----
1733 Br.MaxDisp = (1 << 21) * 2; 0
1734 MI->setDesc(TII->get(ARM::tBfar)); 0
1735 BBInfoVector &BBInfo = BBUtils->getBBInfo(); 0
1736 BBInfo[MBB->getNumber()].Size += 2; 0
1737 BBUtils->adjustBBOffsetsAfter(MBB); 0
1738 ++NumUBrFixed; 0
1739 ----
1740 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Changed B to long jump " << *MI); 0
1741 ----
1742 return true; 0
1743 } ----
1744 ----
1745 /// fixupConditionalBr - Fix up a conditional branch whose destination is too ----
1746 /// far away to fit in its displacement field. It is converted to an inverse ----
1747 /// conditional branch + an unconditional branch to the destination. ----
1748 bool ----
1749 ARMConstantIslands::fixupConditionalBr(ImmBranch &Br) { 0
1750 MachineInstr *MI = Br.MI; 0
1751 MachineBasicBlock *DestBB = MI->getOperand(0).getMBB(); 0
1752 ----
1753 // Add an unconditional branch to the destination and invert the branch ----
1754 // condition to jump over it: ----
1755 // blt L1 ----
1756 // => ----
1757 // bge L2 ----
1758 // b L1 ----
1759 // L2: ----
1760 ARMCC::CondCodes CC = (ARMCC::CondCodes)MI->getOperand(1).getImm(); 0
1761 CC = ARMCC::getOppositeCondition(CC); 0
1762 Register CCReg = MI->getOperand(2).getReg(); 0
1763 ----
1764 // If the branch is at the end of its MBB and that has a fall-through block, ----
1765 // direct the updated conditional branch to the fall-through block. Otherwise, ----
1766 // split the MBB before the next instruction. ----
1767 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI->getParent(); 0
1768 MachineInstr *BMI = &MBB->back(); 0
1769 bool NeedSplit = (BMI != MI) || !BBHasFallthrough(MBB); 0
1770 ----
1771 ++NumCBrFixed; 0
1772 if (BMI != MI) { 0
1773 if (std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)) == std::prev(MBB->end()) && 0
1774 BMI->getOpcode() == Br.UncondBr) { 0
1775 // Last MI in the BB is an unconditional branch. Can we simply invert the ----
1776 // condition and swap destinations: ----
1777 // beq L1 ----
1778 // b L2 ----
1779 // => ----
1780 // bne L2 ----
1781 // b L1 ----
1782 MachineBasicBlock *NewDest = BMI->getOperand(0).getMBB(); 0
1783 if (BBUtils->isBBInRange(MI, NewDest, Br.MaxDisp)) { 0
1784 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1785 dbgs() << " Invert Bcc condition and swap its destination with " ----
1786 << *BMI); ----
1787 BMI->getOperand(0).setMBB(DestBB); 0
1788 MI->getOperand(0).setMBB(NewDest); 0
1789 MI->getOperand(1).setImm(CC); 0
1790 return true; 0
1791 } ----
1792 } ----
1793 } ----
1794 ----
1795 if (NeedSplit) { 0
1796 splitBlockBeforeInstr(MI); 0
1797 // No need for the branch to the next block. We're adding an unconditional ----
1798 // branch to the destination. ----
1799 int delta = TII->getInstSizeInBytes(MBB->back()); 0
1800 BBUtils->adjustBBSize(MBB, -delta); 0
1801 MBB->back().eraseFromParent(); 0
1802 ----
1803 // The conditional successor will be swapped between the BBs after this, so ----
1804 // update CFG. ----
1805 MBB->addSuccessor(DestBB); 0
1806 std::next(MBB->getIterator())->removeSuccessor(DestBB); 0
1807 ----
1808 // BBInfo[SplitBB].Offset is wrong temporarily, fixed below ----
1809 } ----
1810 MachineBasicBlock *NextBB = &*++MBB->getIterator(); 0
1811 ----
1812 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Insert B to " << printMBBReference(*DestBB) 0
1813 << " also invert condition and change dest. to " ----
1814 << printMBBReference(*NextBB) << "\n"); ----
1815 ----
1816 // Insert a new conditional branch and a new unconditional branch. ----
1817 // Also update the ImmBranch as well as adding a new entry for the new branch. ----
1818 BuildMI(MBB, DebugLoc(), TII->get(MI->getOpcode())) 0
1819 .addMBB(NextBB).addImm(CC).addReg(CCReg); 0
1820 Br.MI = &MBB->back(); 0
1821 BBUtils->adjustBBSize(MBB, TII->getInstSizeInBytes(MBB->back())); 0
1822 if (isThumb) 0
1823 BuildMI(MBB, DebugLoc(), TII->get(Br.UncondBr)) 0
1824 .addMBB(DestBB) 0
1825 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
1826 else ----
1827 BuildMI(MBB, DebugLoc(), TII->get(Br.UncondBr)).addMBB(DestBB); 0
1828 BBUtils->adjustBBSize(MBB, TII->getInstSizeInBytes(MBB->back())); 0
1829 unsigned MaxDisp = getUnconditionalBrDisp(Br.UncondBr); 0
1830 ImmBranches.push_back(ImmBranch(&MBB->back(), MaxDisp, false, Br.UncondBr)); 0
1831 ----
1832 // Remove the old conditional branch. It may or may not still be in MBB. ----
1833 BBUtils->adjustBBSize(MI->getParent(), -TII->getInstSizeInBytes(*MI)); 0
1834 MI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1835 BBUtils->adjustBBOffsetsAfter(MBB); 0
1836 return true; 0
1837 } ----
1838 ----
1839 bool ARMConstantIslands::optimizeThumb2Instructions() { 0
1840 bool MadeChange = false; 0
1841 ----
1842 // Shrink ADR and LDR from constantpool. ----
1843 for (CPUser &U : CPUsers) { 0
1844 unsigned Opcode = U.MI->getOpcode(); 0
1845 unsigned NewOpc = 0; 0
1846 unsigned Scale = 1; 0
1847 unsigned Bits = 0; 0
1848 switch (Opcode) { 0
1849 default: break; 0
1850 case ARM::t2LEApcrel: 0
1851 if (isARMLowRegister(U.MI->getOperand(0).getReg())) { 0
1852 NewOpc = ARM::tLEApcrel; 0
1853 Bits = 8; 0
1854 Scale = 4; 0
1855 } ----
1856 break; 0
1857 case ARM::t2LDRpci: 0
1858 if (isARMLowRegister(U.MI->getOperand(0).getReg())) { 0
1859 NewOpc = ARM::tLDRpci; 0
1860 Bits = 8; 0
1861 Scale = 4; 0
1862 } ----
1863 break; 0
1864 } ----
1865 ----
1866 if (!NewOpc) 0
1867 continue; 0
1868 ----
1869 unsigned UserOffset = getUserOffset(U); 0
1870 unsigned MaxOffs = ((1 << Bits) - 1) * Scale; 0
1871 ----
1872 // Be conservative with inline asm. ----
1873 if (!U.KnownAlignment) 0
1874 MaxOffs -= 2; 0
1875 ----
1876 // FIXME: Check if offset is multiple of scale if scale is not 4. ----
1877 if (isCPEntryInRange(U.MI, UserOffset, U.CPEMI, MaxOffs, false, true)) { 0
1878 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Shrink: " << *U.MI); 0
1879 U.MI->setDesc(TII->get(NewOpc)); 0
1880 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = U.MI->getParent(); 0
1881 BBUtils->adjustBBSize(MBB, -2); 0
1882 BBUtils->adjustBBOffsetsAfter(MBB); 0
1883 ++NumT2CPShrunk; 0
1884 MadeChange = true; 0
1885 } ----
1886 } ----
1887 ----
1888 return MadeChange; 0
1889 } ----
1890 ----
1891 ----
1892 bool ARMConstantIslands::optimizeThumb2Branches() { 0
1893 ----
1894 auto TryShrinkBranch = [this](ImmBranch &Br) { 0
1895 unsigned Opcode = Br.MI->getOpcode(); 0
1896 unsigned NewOpc = 0; 0
1897 unsigned Scale = 1; 0
1898 unsigned Bits = 0; 0
1899 switch (Opcode) { 0
1900 default: break; 0
1901 case ARM::t2B: 0
1902 NewOpc = ARM::tB; 0
1903 Bits = 11; 0
1904 Scale = 2; 0
1905 break; 0
1906 case ARM::t2Bcc: 0
1907 NewOpc = ARM::tBcc; 0
1908 Bits = 8; 0
1909 Scale = 2; 0
1910 break; 0
1911 } ----
1912 if (NewOpc) { 0
1913 unsigned MaxOffs = ((1 << (Bits-1))-1) * Scale; 0
1914 MachineBasicBlock *DestBB = Br.MI->getOperand(0).getMBB(); 0
1915 if (BBUtils->isBBInRange(Br.MI, DestBB, MaxOffs)) { 0
1916 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Shrink branch: " << *Br.MI); 0
1917 Br.MI->setDesc(TII->get(NewOpc)); 0
1918 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = Br.MI->getParent(); 0
1919 BBUtils->adjustBBSize(MBB, -2); 0
1920 BBUtils->adjustBBOffsetsAfter(MBB); 0
1921 ++NumT2BrShrunk; 0
1922 return true; 0
1923 } ----
1924 } ----
1925 return false; 0
1926 }; 0
1927 ----
1928 struct ImmCompare { ----
1929 MachineInstr* MI = nullptr; ----
1930 unsigned NewOpc = 0; ----
1931 }; ----
1932 ----
1933 auto FindCmpForCBZ = [this](ImmBranch &Br, ImmCompare &ImmCmp, 0
1934 MachineBasicBlock *DestBB) { 0
1935 ImmCmp.MI = nullptr; 0
1936 ImmCmp.NewOpc = 0; 0
1937 ----
1938 // If the conditional branch doesn't kill CPSR, then CPSR can be liveout ----
1939 // so this transformation is not safe. ----
1940 if (!Br.MI->killsRegister(ARM::CPSR)) 0
1941 return false; 0
1942 ----
1943 Register PredReg; 0
1944 unsigned NewOpc = 0; 0
1945 ARMCC::CondCodes Pred = getInstrPredicate(*Br.MI, PredReg); 0
1946 if (Pred == ARMCC::EQ) 0
1947 NewOpc = ARM::tCBZ; 0
1948 else if (Pred == ARMCC::NE) 0
1949 NewOpc = ARM::tCBNZ; 0
1950 else ----
1951 return false; 0
1952 ----
1953 // Check if the distance is within 126. Subtract starting offset by 2 ----
1954 // because the cmp will be eliminated. ----
1955 unsigned BrOffset = BBUtils->getOffsetOf(Br.MI) + 4 - 2; 0
1956 BBInfoVector &BBInfo = BBUtils->getBBInfo(); 0
1957 unsigned DestOffset = BBInfo[DestBB->getNumber()].Offset; 0
1958 if (BrOffset >= DestOffset || (DestOffset - BrOffset) > 126) 0
1959 return false; 0
1960 ----
1961 // Search backwards to find a tCMPi8 ----
1962 auto *TRI = STI->getRegisterInfo(); 0
1963 MachineInstr *CmpMI = findCMPToFoldIntoCBZ(Br.MI, TRI); 0
1964 if (!CmpMI || CmpMI->getOpcode() != ARM::tCMPi8) 0
1965 return false; 0
1966 ----
1967 ImmCmp.MI = CmpMI; 0
1968 ImmCmp.NewOpc = NewOpc; 0
1969 return true; 0
1970 }; 0
1971 ----
1972 auto TryConvertToLE = [this](ImmBranch &Br, ImmCompare &Cmp) { 0
1973 if (Br.MI->getOpcode() != ARM::t2Bcc || !STI->hasLOB() || 0
1974 STI->hasMinSize()) 0
1975 return false; 0
1976 ----
1977 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = Br.MI->getParent(); 0
1978 MachineBasicBlock *DestBB = Br.MI->getOperand(0).getMBB(); 0
1979 if (BBUtils->getOffsetOf(MBB) < BBUtils->getOffsetOf(DestBB) || 0
1980 !BBUtils->isBBInRange(Br.MI, DestBB, 4094)) 0
1981 return false; 0
1982 ----
1983 if (!DT->dominates(DestBB, MBB)) 0
1984 return false; 0
1985 ----
1986 // We queried for the CBN?Z opcode based upon the 'ExitBB', the opposite ----
1987 // target of Br. So now we need to reverse the condition. ----
1988 Cmp.NewOpc = Cmp.NewOpc == ARM::tCBZ ? ARM::tCBNZ : ARM::tCBZ; 0
1989 ----
1990 MachineInstrBuilder MIB = BuildMI(*MBB, Br.MI, Br.MI->getDebugLoc(), 0
1991 TII->get(ARM::t2LE)); 0
1992 // Swapped a t2Bcc for a t2LE, so no need to update the size of the block. ----
1993 MIB.add(Br.MI->getOperand(0)); 0
1994 Br.MI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1995 Br.MI = MIB; 0
1996 ++NumLEInserted; 0
1997 return true; 0
1998 }; 0
1999 ----
2000 bool MadeChange = false; 0
2001 ----
2002 // The order in which branches appear in ImmBranches is approximately their ----
2003 // order within the function body. By visiting later branches first, we reduce ----
2004 // the distance between earlier forward branches and their targets, making it ----
2005 // more likely that the cbn?z optimization, which can only apply to forward ----
2006 // branches, will succeed. ----
2007 for (ImmBranch &Br : reverse(ImmBranches)) { 0
2008 MachineBasicBlock *DestBB = Br.MI->getOperand(0).getMBB(); 0
2009 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = Br.MI->getParent(); 0
2010 MachineBasicBlock *ExitBB = &MBB->back() == Br.MI ? 0
2011 MBB->getFallThrough() : 0
2012 MBB->back().getOperand(0).getMBB(); 0
2013 ----
2014 ImmCompare Cmp; 0
2015 if (FindCmpForCBZ(Br, Cmp, ExitBB) && TryConvertToLE(Br, Cmp)) { 0
2016 DestBB = ExitBB; 0
2017 MadeChange = true; 0
2018 } else { ----
2019 FindCmpForCBZ(Br, Cmp, DestBB); 0
2020 MadeChange |= TryShrinkBranch(Br); 0
2021 } ----
2022 ----
2023 unsigned Opcode = Br.MI->getOpcode(); 0
2024 if ((Opcode != ARM::tBcc && Opcode != ARM::t2LE) || !Cmp.NewOpc) 0
2025 continue; 0
2026 ----
2027 Register Reg = Cmp.MI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
2028 ----
2029 // Check for Kill flags on Reg. If they are present remove them and set kill ----
2030 // on the new CBZ. ----
2031 auto *TRI = STI->getRegisterInfo(); 0
2032 MachineBasicBlock::iterator KillMI = Br.MI; 0
2033 bool RegKilled = false; 0
2034 do { ----
2035 --KillMI; 0
2036 if (KillMI->killsRegister(Reg, TRI)) { 0
2037 KillMI->clearRegisterKills(Reg, TRI); 0
2038 RegKilled = true; 0
2039 break; 0
2040 } ----
2041 } while (KillMI != Cmp.MI); 0
2042 ----
2043 // Create the new CBZ/CBNZ ----
2044 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Fold: " << *Cmp.MI << " and: " << *Br.MI); 0
2045 MachineInstr *NewBR = ----
2046 BuildMI(*MBB, Br.MI, Br.MI->getDebugLoc(), TII->get(Cmp.NewOpc)) 0
2047 .addReg(Reg, getKillRegState(RegKilled) | 0
2048 getRegState(Cmp.MI->getOperand(0))) 0
2049 .addMBB(DestBB, Br.MI->getOperand(0).getTargetFlags()); 0
2050 ----
2051 Cmp.MI->eraseFromParent(); 0
2052 ----
2053 if (Br.MI->getOpcode() == ARM::tBcc) { 0
2054 Br.MI->eraseFromParent(); 0
2055 Br.MI = NewBR; 0
2056 BBUtils->adjustBBSize(MBB, -2); 0
2057 } else if (MBB->back().getOpcode() != ARM::t2LE) { 0
2058 // An LE has been generated, but it's not the terminator - that is an ----
2059 // unconditional branch. However, the logic has now been reversed with the ----
2060 // CBN?Z being the conditional branch and the LE being the unconditional ----
2061 // branch. So this means we can remove the redundant unconditional branch ----
2062 // at the end of the block. ----
2063 MachineInstr *LastMI = &MBB->back(); 0
2064 BBUtils->adjustBBSize(MBB, -LastMI->getDesc().getSize()); 0
2065 LastMI->eraseFromParent(); 0
2066 } ----
2067 BBUtils->adjustBBOffsetsAfter(MBB); 0
2068 ++NumCBZ; 0
2069 MadeChange = true; 0
2070 } ----
2071 ----
2072 return MadeChange; 0
2073 } ----
2074 ----
2075 static bool isSimpleIndexCalc(MachineInstr &I, unsigned EntryReg, 0
2076 unsigned BaseReg) { ----
2077 if (I.getOpcode() != ARM::t2ADDrs) 0
2078 return false; 0
2079 ----
2080 if (I.getOperand(0).getReg() != EntryReg) 0
2081 return false; 0
2082 ----
2083 if (I.getOperand(1).getReg() != BaseReg) 0
2084 return false; 0
2085 ----
2086 // FIXME: what about CC and IdxReg? ----
2087 return true; 0
2088 } ----
2089 ----
2090 /// While trying to form a TBB/TBH instruction, we may (if the table ----
2091 /// doesn't immediately follow the BR_JT) need access to the start of the ----
2092 /// jump-table. We know one instruction that produces such a register; this ----
2093 /// function works out whether that definition can be preserved to the BR_JT, ----
2094 /// possibly by removing an intervening addition (which is usually needed to ----
2095 /// calculate the actual entry to jump to). ----
2096 bool ARMConstantIslands::preserveBaseRegister(MachineInstr *JumpMI, 0
2097 MachineInstr *LEAMI, ----
2098 unsigned &DeadSize, ----
2099 bool &CanDeleteLEA, ----
2100 bool &BaseRegKill) { ----
2101 if (JumpMI->getParent() != LEAMI->getParent()) 0
2102 return false; 0
2103 ----
2104 // Now we hope that we have at least these instructions in the basic block: ----
2105 // BaseReg = t2LEA ... ----
2106 // [...] ----
2107 // EntryReg = t2ADDrs BaseReg, ... ----
2108 // [...] ----
2109 // t2BR_JT EntryReg ----
2110 // ----
2111 // We have to be very conservative about what we recognise here though. The ----
2112 // main perturbing factors to watch out for are: ----
2113 // + Spills at any point in the chain: not direct problems but we would ----
2114 // expect a blocking Def of the spilled register so in practice what we ----
2115 // can do is limited. ----
2116 // + EntryReg == BaseReg: this is the one situation we should allow a Def ----
2117 // of BaseReg, but only if the t2ADDrs can be removed. ----
2118 // + Some instruction other than t2ADDrs computing the entry. Not seen in ----
2119 // the wild, but we should be careful. ----
2120 Register EntryReg = JumpMI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
2121 Register BaseReg = LEAMI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
2122 ----
2123 CanDeleteLEA = true; 0
2124 BaseRegKill = false; 0
2125 MachineInstr *RemovableAdd = nullptr; 0
2126 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I(LEAMI); 0
2127 for (++I; &*I != JumpMI; ++I) { 0
2128 if (isSimpleIndexCalc(*I, EntryReg, BaseReg)) { 0
2129 RemovableAdd = &*I; 0
2130 break; 0
2131 } ----
2132 ----
2133 for (const MachineOperand &MO : I->operands()) { 0
2134 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.getReg()) 0
2135 continue; 0
2136 if (MO.isDef() && MO.getReg() == BaseReg) 0
2137 return false; 0
2138 if (MO.isUse() && MO.getReg() == BaseReg) { 0
2139 BaseRegKill = BaseRegKill || MO.isKill(); 0
2140 CanDeleteLEA = false; 0
2141 } ----
2142 } ----
2143 } ----
2144 ----
2145 if (!RemovableAdd) 0
2146 return true; 0
2147 ----
2148 // Check the add really is removable, and that nothing else in the block ----
2149 // clobbers BaseReg. ----
2150 for (++I; &*I != JumpMI; ++I) { 0
2151 for (const MachineOperand &MO : I->operands()) { 0
2152 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.getReg()) 0
2153 continue; 0
2154 if (MO.isDef() && MO.getReg() == BaseReg) 0
2155 return false; 0
2156 if (MO.isUse() && MO.getReg() == EntryReg) 0
2157 RemovableAdd = nullptr; 0
2158 } ----
2159 } ----
2160 ----
2161 if (RemovableAdd) { 0
2162 RemovableAdd->eraseFromParent(); 0
2163 DeadSize += isThumb2 ? 4 : 2; 0
2164 } else if (BaseReg == EntryReg) { 0
2165 // The add wasn't removable, but clobbered the base for the TBB. So we can't ----
2166 // preserve it. ----
2167 return false; 0
2168 } ----
2169 ----
2170 // We reached the end of the block without seeing another definition of ----
2171 // BaseReg (except, possibly the t2ADDrs, which was removed). BaseReg can be ----
2172 // used in the TBB/TBH if necessary. ----
2173 return true; 0
2174 } ----
2175 ----
2176 /// Returns whether CPEMI is the first instruction in the block ----
2177 /// immediately following JTMI (assumed to be a TBB or TBH terminator). If so, ----
2178 /// we can switch the first register to PC and usually remove the address ----
2179 /// calculation that preceded it. ----
2180 static bool jumpTableFollowsTB(MachineInstr *JTMI, MachineInstr *CPEMI) { 0
2181 MachineFunction::iterator MBB = JTMI->getParent()->getIterator(); 0
2182 MachineFunction *MF = MBB->getParent(); 0
2183 ++MBB; 0
2184 ----
2185 return MBB != MF->end() && !MBB->empty() && &*MBB->begin() == CPEMI; 0
2186 } ----
2187 ----
2188 static void RemoveDeadAddBetweenLEAAndJT(MachineInstr *LEAMI, 0
2189 MachineInstr *JumpMI, ----
2190 unsigned &DeadSize) { ----
2191 // Remove a dead add between the LEA and JT, which used to compute EntryReg, ----
2192 // but the JT now uses PC. Finds the last ADD (if any) that def's EntryReg ----
2193 // and is not clobbered / used. ----
2194 MachineInstr *RemovableAdd = nullptr; 0
2195 Register EntryReg = JumpMI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
2196 ----
2197 // Find the last ADD to set EntryReg ----
2198 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I(LEAMI); 0
2199 for (++I; &*I != JumpMI; ++I) { 0
2200 if (I->getOpcode() == ARM::t2ADDrs && I->getOperand(0).getReg() == EntryReg) 0
2201 RemovableAdd = &*I; 0
2202 } ----
2203 ----
2204 if (!RemovableAdd) 0
2205 return; 0
2206 ----
2207 // Ensure EntryReg is not clobbered or used. ----
2208 MachineBasicBlock::iterator J(RemovableAdd); 0
2209 for (++J; &*J != JumpMI; ++J) { 0
2210 for (const MachineOperand &MO : J->operands()) { 0
2211 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.getReg()) 0
2212 continue; 0
2213 if (MO.isDef() && MO.getReg() == EntryReg) 0
2214 return; 0
2215 if (MO.isUse() && MO.getReg() == EntryReg) 0
2216 return; 0
2217 } ----
2218 } ----
2219 ----
2220 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Removing Dead Add: " << *RemovableAdd); 0
2221 RemovableAdd->eraseFromParent(); 0
2222 DeadSize += 4; 0
2223 } ----
2224 ----
2225 /// optimizeThumb2JumpTables - Use tbb / tbh instructions to generate smaller ----
2226 /// jumptables when it's possible. ----
2227 bool ARMConstantIslands::optimizeThumb2JumpTables() { 0
2228 bool MadeChange = false; 0
2229 ----
2230 // FIXME: After the tables are shrunk, can we get rid some of the ----
2231 // constantpool tables? ----
2232 MachineJumpTableInfo *MJTI = MF->getJumpTableInfo(); 0
2233 if (!MJTI) return false; 0
2234 ----
2235 const std::vector &JT = MJTI->getJumpTables(); 0
2236 for (unsigned i = 0, e = T2JumpTables.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
2237 MachineInstr *MI = T2JumpTables[i]; 0
2238 const MCInstrDesc &MCID = MI->getDesc(); 0
2239 unsigned NumOps = MCID.getNumOperands(); 0
2240 unsigned JTOpIdx = NumOps - (MI->isPredicable() ? 2 : 1); 0
2241 MachineOperand JTOP = MI->getOperand(JTOpIdx); 0
2242 unsigned JTI = JTOP.getIndex(); 0
2243 assert(JTI < JT.size()); 0
2244 ----
2245 bool ByteOk = true; 0
2246 bool HalfWordOk = true; 0
2247 unsigned JTOffset = BBUtils->getOffsetOf(MI) + 4; 0
2248 const std::vector &JTBBs = JT[JTI].MBBs; 0
2249 BBInfoVector &BBInfo = BBUtils->getBBInfo(); 0

2423 /// reorderThumb2JumpTables - Adjust the function's block layout to ensure that ----
2424 /// jump tables always branch forwards, since that's what tbb and tbh need. ----

2464 MachineBasicBlock *ARMConstantIslands::adjustJTTargetBlockForward( 0
2465 unsigned JTI, MachineBasicBlock *BB, MachineBasicBlock *JTBB) { ----
2466 // If the destination block is terminated by an unconditional branch, ----
2467 // try to move it; otherwise, create a new block following the jump ----
2468 // table that branches back to the actual target. This is a very simple ----
2469 // heuristic. FIXME: We can definitely improve it. ----
2470 MachineBasicBlock *TBB = nullptr, *FBB = nullptr; 0
2471 SmallVector Cond; 0
2472 SmallVector CondPrior; 0
2473 MachineFunction::iterator BBi = BB->getIterator(); 0
2474 MachineFunction::iterator OldPrior = std::prev(BBi); 0
2475 MachineFunction::iterator OldNext = std::next(BBi); 0
2476 ----
2477 // If the block terminator isn't analyzable, don't try to move the block ----
2478 bool B = TII->analyzeBranch(*BB, TBB, FBB, Cond); 0
2479 ----
2480 // If the block ends in an unconditional branch, move it. The prior block ----
2481 // has to have an analyzable terminator for us to move this one. Be paranoid ----
2482 // and make sure we're not trying to move the entry block of the function. ----
2483 if (!B && Cond.empty() && BB != &MF->front() && 0
2484 !TII->analyzeBranch(*OldPrior, TBB, FBB, CondPrior)) { 0
2485 BB->moveAfter(JTBB); 0
2486 OldPrior->updateTerminator(BB); 0
2487 BB->updateTerminator(OldNext != MF->end() ? &*OldNext : nullptr); 0
2488 // Update numbering to account for the block being moved. ----
2489 MF->RenumberBlocks(); 0
2490 ++NumJTMoved; 0
2491 return nullptr; 0
2492 } ----
2493 ----
2494 // Create a new MBB for the code after the jump BB. ----
2495 MachineBasicBlock *NewBB = ----
2496 MF->CreateMachineBasicBlock(JTBB->getBasicBlock()); 0
2497 MachineFunction::iterator MBBI = ++JTBB->getIterator(); 0
2498 MF->insert(MBBI, NewBB); 0
2499 ----
2500 // Copy live-in information to new block. ----
2501 for (const MachineBasicBlock::RegisterMaskPair &RegMaskPair : BB->liveins()) 0
2502 NewBB->addLiveIn(RegMaskPair); 0
2503 ----
2504 // Add an unconditional branch from NewBB to BB. ----
2505 // There doesn't seem to be meaningful DebugInfo available; this doesn't ----
2506 // correspond directly to anything in the source. ----
2507 if (isThumb2) 0
2508 BuildMI(NewBB, DebugLoc(), TII->get(ARM::t2B)) 0
2509 .addMBB(BB) 0
2510 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
2511 else ----
2512 BuildMI(NewBB, DebugLoc(), TII->get(ARM::tB)) 0
2513 .addMBB(BB) 0
2514 .add(predOps(ARMCC::AL)); 0
2515 ----
2516 // Update internal data structures to account for the newly inserted MBB. ----
2517 MF->RenumberBlocks(NewBB); 0
2518 ----
2519 // Update the CFG. ----
2520 NewBB->addSuccessor(BB); 0
2521 JTBB->replaceSuccessor(BB, NewBB); 0
2522 ----
2523 ++NumJTInserted; 0
2524 return NewBB; 0
2525 } 0
